Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.39,0:00:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be pretty excited, Sakata-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.56,0:00:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You've appointed Iwata-san the dispatched roundtable moderator, {派遣幹部 - basically toda can't attend all those roundtables himself so he trains new leaders to organize discussions for him and sends them out, unsure if moderator is a fitting word}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.57,0:00:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so I decided I also need\Nto rise to his level as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:55.01,Top,,0,0,0,,I see. Good to know our young men department is so full of vim and vigor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.01,0:00:59.72,Top,,0,0,0,,But Iwata also needs to learn to control himself, let's not forget that. {/if you're too authoritative/bossy that's a problem too, like in iwata's case}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.62,0:01:01.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,January 1949 \NSoka Gakkai Headquarters {1949年(昭和24年)1月\N創価学会本部}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.60,0:01:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't let your authoritative role go to your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.70,0:01:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, you kept talking to yourself for hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.59,0:01:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A roundtable discussion \Nis where everyone can have a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.21,0:01:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! \NI'll pay more attention now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.43,0:01:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa there, no need to put on \Nsuch an intimidating look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.65,0:01:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be sure to scare everyone away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Roundtable discussions \Nare not just for young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.04,0:01:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome the newcomers and young ladies as well. {unsure why "new members" are something different from young men and young women}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.21,0:01:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The society may become an infinitely dark and bleak place, but our meetings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.69,0:01:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,must remain the beacon \Nof light and hope for the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.26,0:01:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,where the most courageous conversations take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.25,0:01:45.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Around that time, Soka Gakkai was actively intensifying its roundtable-related activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.98,0:01:50.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As many as 38 roundtable discussions \Nwere held every month
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.40,0:01:53.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at locations in Tokyo and nearby prefectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:57.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since the beginning of that year, Toda had been training and nurturing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:00.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the new roundtable moderators \Nto attend those in his stead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:10.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Morikawa-kun had hardly been showing up since this year started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.21,0:02:13.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,I hear he's starting a diner...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.38,0:02:17.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't help but wonder about his family's circumstances and if his piety stands strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.72,0:02:22.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,Besides, the members of our Tsurumi Branch \Nmust be very upset to hear that Morikawa-kun, {unsure what he means, just says "members of tsurumi" but tsurumi is a town so idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.70,0:02:27.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,a man of pure faith, \Nhas been fired from his company.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.25,0:02:43.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Three Meals a Day Coupon {Take Out }Diner {not sure what to call it, coupon diners were instituted in 1942, they kinda worked like rationing to feed factory workers so that they don't have to cook for themselves, existed until 1951 when rationing was finally deprecated; 三食外食券食堂}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.73,0:02:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.66,0:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry for not visiting you in a long while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming all the way to Tsurumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.75,0:02:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Missus!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.42,0:02:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm out of soy sauce!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.38,0:02:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.01,0:03:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.33,0:03:07.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Morikawa Koji, the linchpin of the Tsurumi Branch in Kanagawa Prefecture, {again, doesn't say branch just says "central figure in tsurumi of kanagawa" - I don't think he was the centerpiece of an entire town}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:11.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Credit Union "Hope" {/kibou}{希望信用組合}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.27,0:03:11.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,resigned from the credit union where he had worked for many years, just last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.23,0:03:17.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The union executives, repulsed by Morikawa's strong sense of justice and outspoken opinions,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.48,0:03:19.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,conspired to force him to resign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.85,0:03:22.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They made it look like he asked for a resignation himself. {lit: It was a polite-sounding; plausible (e.g. excuse) layoff, so to speak - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.49,0:03:26.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Morikawa then began operating a diner, something he was not accustomed to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:28.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in the hope of doing something \Nto help people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.84,0:03:31.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in these times when food was scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.84,0:03:31.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,Restaurant Ichiba {市場食堂}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Morikawa-kun, \Nis your business going well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It brings in just enough to keep my family fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, it's such an honor to have you \Ncome to our roundtable discussion today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you kindly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'm just glad to see you're doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.84,0:03:55.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,Morikawa-kun is the same as usual, \Nnothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.23,0:03:57.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,The real problem will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.06,0:04:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,As you probably know, \NMorikawa-kun was fired from his company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.25,0:04:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you find it strange that it happened
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to someone whose faith was so strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.03,0:04:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.53,0:04:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, to be honest, \NI do find it troubling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.73,0:04:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At a roundtable discussion, Morikawa-san said, \N"I was fired from my company,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.17,0:04:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll try to turn this poison into medicine."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.57,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when everyone's faith \Nbegan to waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.94,0:04:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't speak for everyone, \Njust because your own faith did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.01,0:04:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"With faith, I'll turn poison into medicine."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:48.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,Turn poison into medicine {変毒為薬}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the merits of Buddha, \Nand through our faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we can transform poison into something beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it sound natural to you? \NIf so, how can it make your faith waver?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.37,0:04:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you don't understand what faith is?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.42,0:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I do understand that. \NIn his scriptures, {/Gosho}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.86,0:05:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren states, \N"Once you turn to the Buddha, {/start practicing the Buddha Dharma; look my notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.18,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the three obstacles and four devils \Nwill start fighting within you." {https://agoshoaday.wordpress.com/buddhist-concepts/three-obstacles-and-four-devils/}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.37,0:05:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is easy to understand through reason, but that is not the same as understanding it through faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.38,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you just say that what happened to Morikawa is troubling?'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you truly understood it, \Nyou wouldn't be complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.89,0:05:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, you don't understand, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.35,0:05:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not Morikawa-kun I'm worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.91,0:05:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you, our Tsurumi followers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.36,0:05:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,While amusing yourselves at the fact Morikawa was fired for his strong faith, {/finding it strange that ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.45,0:05:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,not a single one of you \Ncame to me for guidance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.05,0:05:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, when you get together, \Nyou call it "troubling"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and use it as a pretext \Nto criticize and doubt each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what scares me the most \Nas a Buddhist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.84,0:06:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If something were to happen to you, \Nyou'd accept it as Buddha's will. {lit: if it's about yourself, you accept that buddha is the root of all things}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.33,0:06:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it becomes another's lot, \Ndoubting and losing your own faith... {idling in one's training; backsliding; retrogression (to a lower level of religious practice)​}{I think he means "if something happens to you, you think "well it's my fault and god's will" and when it's another you think "we'll it's his fault for not believing hard enough/believing the wrong god/etc" which makes sense... if you think about it hard enough from a buddhist's perspective}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is the most foolish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.77,0:06:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd hate to see you behave so foolishly, my friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.61,0:06:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did that give you a better understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Morikawa-kun's problem has already been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.26,0:06:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll understand it once you've observed it for a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.02,0:06:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank god, you're still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kazumasa-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:45.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,While they were seeing him off, {on the way  to the station}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.32,0:06:50.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda gave Morikawa and his eldest son Kazumasa guidance and encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.36,0:06:54.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And just as Toda had said, within a year, Morikawa Koji
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.99,0:07:01.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was offered a position on favorable terms \Nat a credit union in Kawasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:06.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nihon Shogakkan (Soka Gakkai Headquarters) {日本正学館(創価学会本部)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I got us the illustrations \Nand a manuscript of a short story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I also got him to agree to write a serialized novel for our new project.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.93,0:07:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.89,0:07:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really get that writer \Nto work with us at our manuscript fee?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.72,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I told him about the editorial policy of “Adventure Boy”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and my personal vision for the magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.60,0:07:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When I finished, he said, \N"Okay, I understand," and graciously agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.46,0:07:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the Great White Lotus project. {notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.88,0:07:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:51.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was decided to publish a new journal, \N"The Great White Lotus,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.37,0:07:53.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in place of "Value Creation" journal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:59.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so a planning meeting was held \Nwith Konishi, Yamadaira and other editors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We should by all means include
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.65,0:08:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a column for personal experiences and one for refuting the dogmas of other sects.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think the false religious views \Nof a modern man come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.91,0:08:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think bringing that to light
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.85,0:08:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is the mission of the Great White Lotus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.99,0:08:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira-kun, I agree with you and I support that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.71,0:08:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's consider it for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.74,0:08:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be sure our readers will appreciate that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.63,0:08:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming self-righteous in image, \Nlike all the other sects, won't do us any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.99,0:08:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose... You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The days of saying this and that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in a language that only our fellow academics and clergy can understand are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.01,0:08:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're long past the times when you could merely provide
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.06,0:08:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,arguments that only work in the religious plane and call it a day. {/logic only applicable to religion is no longer valid}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.37,0:08:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to be more vocal, broaden our horizons, open our doors to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.36,0:08:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not make the magazine available to all kinds of educated people, or just those {/specialists in various fields}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.70,0:09:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with the history of Buddhism? {unsure: さまざまな分野の専門家や仏教史に通じた人たちにも 誌面を提供してはどうだろうかね?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.44,0:09:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are anxious about how it'll turn out, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Worry not, for Buddhism encompasses all schools of thought and philosophies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.08,0:09:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That holistic nature is the main strength \Nof the Buddha Dharma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.10,0:09:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll write for it myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.43,0:09:31.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,Toda
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.45,0:09:33.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Late at night, Toda was at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:36.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,working on a philosophical article, \N"The Theory of Life,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.93,0:09:40.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to be published in The Great White Lotus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:40.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Theory of Life {生命論}\NToda Josei {below}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.27,0:09:41.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Jintan}{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jintan_(Japanese_medicine)}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:09:58.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.89,0:10:03.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Back then, I was also confined to a small room like this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.72,0:10:06.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,pacing back and forth \Nlike an animal in a cage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:09.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,March 1944 \NSugamo Tokyo Detention House {1944年3月(昭和19年)\N巣鴨・東京拘置所}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,The opening text of the Lotus Sutra, \Nthe Innumerable Meanings Sutra {無量義経}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:17.36,Top,,0,0,0,,I lose the thread whenever I get to this piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.89,0:10:22.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,34 negations in a row... {/"not's" (非)}{https://www.joseitoda.org/resources/essays/buddhaaslife.html}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.02,0:10:28.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,What purpose does this passage serve? \NI just don't understand it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.07,0:10:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.09,0:10:39.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Starting from New Year's Day, Toda resolved to chant and recite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.08,0:10:43.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Lotus Sutra prayer 10,000 times a day \Nand he stuck to this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.31,0:10:48.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He had already reread the Lotus Sutra three times and was now
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:51.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,on his fourth attempt in March.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:58.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And when he was once again faced with a Sutra \Nwith 34 "not's" written across 12 lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.65,0:11:06.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he resolved not to go a single step further until he could be sure that he understands it fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:10.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,His body is neither present nor absent... {written in old, extremely concise language but idk how to convey it}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.88,0:11:16.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have a physical body. \NYes he's not immaterial either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.88,0:11:22.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Buddha's body in this world is not something that exists, nor is it something nonexistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:27.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,Something that's not there... \NSomething that's not absent...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.57,0:11:34.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not square, nor is it round. \NIt's not short, nor is it long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.40,0:11:40.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,It can't move, it can't roll, \Nneither is it immovable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:43.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,What on earth could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:46.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:52.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,These 34 negations cannot be just meaningless padding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.31,0:11:57.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,He's definitely describing something that does exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.88,0:11:59.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.34,0:12:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.40,0:12:19.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Late March {3月下旬一}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.82,0:12:27.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not present, \Nneither is it absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.01,0:12:29.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,Not square, \Nneither round.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.64,0:12:32.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,Not short, \Nnor long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.12,0:12:35.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,What on Earth is he trying to describe?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.83,0:12:39.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,There is absolutely no way that the Lotus Sutra is just an idealistic chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.41,0:12:42.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Buddha's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:46.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,It can't be something so mysterious \Nyou can't even imagine it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.30,0:12:52.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not created artificially. \NNor did it appear spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.45,0:12:57.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's not moving, \Nneither does it stand still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.40,0:13:00.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,And it definitely has to be real...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.88,0:13:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:13.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,{The Buddha's body is }Neither present nor absent
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:16.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.93,0:13:18.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.64,0:13:23.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it! It's the life! \NIt's the quality of being alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.95,0:13:25.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.53,0:13:29.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,His body... The Buddha himself \Nis the epitome of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.46,0:13:33.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was looking for something that's outside, \Nbut it's the very life of mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.46,0:13:33.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,Life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:41.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,No! He is present outside too! \NHe embodies all life in the universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:03.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Buddha is life itself,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.77,0:14:07.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,having concluded that, Toda finally read through all the 34 negations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:10.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and could continue reading the Lotus Sutra.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.13,0:14:18.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Around this time, \Na new question formed in Toda's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:21.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,That said, what exactly did the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:26.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,want to teach us through these 28 chapters of the Lotus Sutra?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:31.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,If the Lotus Sutra is the most important sacred teaching of Buddhism, then what is its essence?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:35.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,What is the truth of the Lotus Sutra?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.03,0:14:38.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This second question became Toda's new obsession. {actually "theme"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:44.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Awake or asleep, he kept asking himself, "What is the essence of the Lotus Sutra?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.34,0:14:47.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He spent days chanting and meditating, \Ntrying to uncover the answer. {/approach the theme}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.63,0:14:51.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In mid-November, the number of times he chanted the Sutra
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.41,0:14:54.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,since the New Year's Day was approaching two million.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:55.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On one such morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.32,0:15:12.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,What a refreshing feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.56,0:15:17.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:28.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, \Nit's the Buddha Realm. {actually "虚空会 / the kokue ritual" but it's fairly obscure even in japanese, look notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.59,0:15:32.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,All the Bodhisattvas of the Earth are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.55,0:15:35.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I am one of them right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.46,0:15:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.52,0:16:05.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NThere's nothing strange about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:08.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,All the countless Bodhisattvas of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.92,0:16:11.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,numbering 60,000 times the grains of sand of the Ganges River... {look notes}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.63,0:16:13.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:16.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,And the head priest, \Nthe Ascended Bodhisattva... {unsure: そして上首・上行菩薩は まさしく 日蓮大聖人であったはずだ!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.43,0:16:19.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was none other \Nthan Nichiren Daishonin himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:24.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,"Sacred Mountain Meeting \NStands Solemnly Strong."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:28.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,The meeting at the sacred mountain still stands strong and has not yet dispersed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:32.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's it. \NMy whole life is decided now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:39.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will spend the rest of my days \Nspreading this precious Great Law!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.65,0:16:43.50,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At the same time, old and ill, \NMakiguchi Tsunesaburo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:46.29,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,was held in a solitary cell \Nof a separate building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.29,0:16:49.83,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Infirmity and malnutrition exacted a heavy toll on Makiguchi's health,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:17:01.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi Tsunesaburo, \Nfirst president of the Soka Gakkai {創価学会 初代会長牧口常三郎}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:54.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,so on November 17th, he moved voluntarily to a hospital room within the detention center.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.97,0:16:57.64,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And on the following day, the 18th,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.64,0:17:01.67,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,he passed away peacefully \Nat the end of his noble, 73-year-long life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.30,0:17:07.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At that time, Toda had no way of knowing about Makiguchi's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.06,0:17:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha, Daishonin-sama, \NI am grateful to no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.68,0:17:18.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Having realized the mysterious reality of life through his "enlightenment in prison," Toda
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.16,0:17:23.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,proceeded to describe his experience in the opening article of "The Great White Lotus."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.45,0:17:27.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,While many armchair theorists \Nphilosophize for the sake of philosophizing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.42,0:17:30.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda positioned his paper \Nas applied philosophy. {/practical }
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:38.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda's strong yearning for the happiness of all people led to the creation of his chef-d'oeuvre,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.33,0:17:41.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the philosophical treatise \N"The Theory of Life,"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:46.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which would go on to open the way to the Buddhist Dharma for the broad masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.85,0:17:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that should be enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.11,0:17:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:01.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,Late June {6月下旬一}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.31,0:18:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call it a day, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei! Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We finished printing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.77,0:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it came out nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:25.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The long-awaited new journal from Soka Gakkai, \NThe Great White Lotus, has been delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:33.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first issue, freshly printed, was distributed ahead of its publication date of July 10, 1949.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.93,0:18:37.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda and the Soka Gakkai members were overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.25,0:18:41.73,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Brandenburg Gates
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.73,0:18:45.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Germany splits into East and West. Conflict deepens. {ドイツ、東西に分裂。対立深まる}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.17,0:18:47.83,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The conflict between East and West \Nis growing ever-deeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:49.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,Communist offensive continues on the Chinese mainland {中国大陸で共産軍の攻勢続く}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:56.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,The Soviet Union tests its first atomic bomb in the Central Asian desert {ソ連、中央アジアの砂漠で初の原爆実験}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:54.50,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Soviet Union announces possession of atomic weapons to contain the threat from the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:56.99,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The Cold War is growing more and more intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:19:00.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,Hibiya GHQ (Allied Powers High Command) {日比谷 GHQ(連合国軍総司令部)}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:19:00.95,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Compelled to change its occupation policy towards Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:05.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,{above}Japan is a barrier against the eastward advance of communism, General MacArthur declares{日本は赤化東進の防壁\Nマッカーサー元帥声明}\N{right, vertical}Belief in the role of the national assembly in promoting peace, not just propaganda {宣傳に搖がぬ國民集團平和の役割惟信}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.95,0:19:05.47,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and turn it into a bulwark against communism, the US orders the Japanese government
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:10.71,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,to enact the "Nine Principles for Economic Stability," also known as Dodge Plan. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodge_Line}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.46,0:19:10.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,Minister and Economic Adviser to the Supreme Commander for the Allied Powers, Dodge (GHQ) {GHQ連合国総司令部ドッジ公使・経済顧問}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:13.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nine principles for economic stability {経済安定九原則}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:14.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,It hastened the recovery of Japanese economy's self-reliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:15.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,JNR issues first round of layoff notice to 30,700 employees yesterday {國鉄 解雇を通達すきのう第一次三万七百名}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.98,0:19:18.01,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And for that reason, the society...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.59,0:19:18.01,Sign,,0,0,0,,Deflationary 42 billion yen: \Nnext year's funding program {通貨收縮四百廿億 明年度資金計画}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:20.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nippon Electric to lay off 3,000 employees; \Nproposes downsizing to union {日電 三千名整理へ\N組合側に経営縮小を提示}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.21,0:19:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,More returns! {books returned unsold}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're seeing a gradual increase in returns,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if we keep ending up in the red, \Nthe banks won't give us any more loans. {/if we're considered a nonperforming company}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.92,0:19:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.89,0:19:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As I've been saying for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the days when you could make anything and it would sell are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.55,0:19:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, if we don't do something about it, \Nwe'll all end up on the street!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.18,0:19:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I heard you. \NWe'll come up with something good to make. {lit: first, make a good thing - as opposed to "anything" because it no longer sells}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.52,0:19:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll see what we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.82,0:19:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting on you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:12.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,The one thing selling well now \Nis the "Adventure Boy."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.69,0:20:17.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Women's magazine "Ruby" is in decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.42,0:20:21.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, Mishima-kun was not cut out to work on periodicals, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.05,0:20:24.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'll try to put the young Sato-kun in charge of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.39,0:20:26.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,As for the Boys' magazines...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.53,0:20:31.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yamamoto-kun might be able to breathe new life into it with his insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.14,0:20:33.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's gotten used to this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, time to appoint him \Nas the editor-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.19,0:20:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto-kun, I got a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.27,0:20:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As the editor-in-chief, please create a good magazine that promotes the children's dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.41,0:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it also has to sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.32,0:20:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is not to say you must pander to the whims of the market. {/world}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.78,0:20:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it the outlet for your own ideas\Nand shape it according to your vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.84,0:20:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. I will make every effort \Nto live up to your expectations!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:02.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{above}Kanda Bookstore {神田書房}\N{below left}Nakamoto Bookstore {中本書店}\N{below middle}Takayama Bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:09.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's my first serious work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.87,0:21:09.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,Adventure Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.21,0:21:11.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad to see that it sells well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:15.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must meet Toda-sensei's expectations no matter the cost...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.45,0:21:21.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,Make "Adventure Boy" the number one boys' magazine in Japan, beloved by the children!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.39,0:21:28.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,An editorial meeting was held.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.35,0:21:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.90,0:21:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking of changing the name of the magazine...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.36,0:21:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So what do you have in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.36,0:21:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"Japan's Boy."{actually 少年日本 = "Boy Japan" so idk what to make it}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to express my hope that Japan will open up to the future at the hands of young boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.30,0:21:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.30,0:21:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Japan's Boy," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.14,0:21:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, it does have a meaningful and powerful ring to it. Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.06,0:21:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a name with a much broader scope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.13,0:21:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.04,0:22:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Let's go with "Japan's Boy" \Nstarting next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.91,0:22:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Any ideas on how to capture the readers' attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.64,0:22:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Here's my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:10.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi spoke of his \Nnew idea and a way to realize it -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.73,0:22:15.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,magazine supplements: adding value \Nby changing the binding size.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.81,0:22:20.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He went on to explain that this would help to engage the children's minds. {/capture attention of}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.42,0:22:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I like that. \NLet's go with your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.66,0:22:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.33,0:22:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got that. \NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I like baseball.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.04,0:22:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a huge fan of Kawakami from Giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.55,0:22:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You like baseball, then?\NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Learning about the great minds of the world, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.65,0:22:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want a book that teaches me something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.57,0:22:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Next month, we'll be launching a magazine called "Japan's Boy"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.97,0:22:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that'll contain all the suggestions \Nfrom you guys. {/with all the things you wanna read}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.18,0:23:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure to read it. {/support it}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.48,0:23:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sounds good!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.24,0:23:12.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,The illustrations in this issue \Nare very well done. Way to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.00,0:23:17.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.85,0:23:20.72,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Yamaoka Sohachi's \Nserialized historical novel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.72,0:23:24.19,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,"The Three Red-Faced Swordsmen" \Nenjoys popularity among children. {I can't find any work of such name, copyright maybe? ; 紅顏三剣士 ; https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%B1%B1%E5%B2%A1%E8%8D%98%E5%85%AB}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.19,0:23:27.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,Sohachi Yamaoka \NRepresentative work: The epic novel "Tokugawa Ieyasu" {it'll be 3 more years until it's published lol}{山岡荘八氏\N代表作-大河小説「徳川家康」}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:27.18,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,I'm sure everyone is looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.18,0:23:30.17,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Next is Nomura-sensei's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.17,0:23:36.14,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Shinichi had also commissioned a manuscript from the historical novelist Nomura Kodo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.17,0:23:38.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nomura Kodo \NRepresentative work: "Zenigata Heiji's Detective Memoirs" {野村胡堂氏\N代表作-「銭形平次捕物控」}{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E9%8A%AD%E5%BD%A2%E5%B9%B3%E6%AC%A1%E6%8D%95%E7%89%A9%E6%8E%A7}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.91,0:23:52.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,New publication announcement: Japan's Boys {新刊 ; 少年日本}\NRevised title of the "Adventure Boy" {冒険少年改訂題}\NPen drawings collection from the six great artists {六大画家ペン画集}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.01,0:23:55.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.22,0:24:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There! I take the rook. Checkmate!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.19,0:24:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.54,0:24:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.70,0:24:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not waiting. Not taking it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.50,Overlap,,0,0,0,,This is Yamamoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.19,0:24:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.65,0:24:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, thank you for the ads campaign!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.66,0:24:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I thought we can afford splurging a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.53,0:24:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, by the way, I approve the general plan for the New Year's issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.43,0:24:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.25,0:24:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Preparing the new year's issue already?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.44,0:24:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Famous writers \Nare always in high demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.15,0:24:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to start preparing \Nand negotiating now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.18,0:24:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? I must say, Yamamoto-kun seems like a hardworking young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.58,0:24:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he still only 21?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.56,0:24:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's our young editor-in-chief, though we only hired him half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.86,0:24:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He's giving his all to "Japan's Boy," \Nwants to make it Japan's #1 magazine for boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.91,0:24:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew something had changed. {no clue what he means: やっぱり違うね}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.44,0:25:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's focus on roundtable discussions next month as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.93,0:25:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.76,0:25:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been trying to find a way to increase the reach of our lectures on the greatness of Buddha {/roundtable discussions}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.64,0:25:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by organizing internal meetings within the Youth Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.23,0:25:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, the number of participants, both the regulars and newcomers, is decreasing lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.42,0:25:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.38,0:25:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I wish you all great inspiration! {/for you to stir up/rouse yourself}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.65,0:25:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't everyone here lacking in spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.40,0:25:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What we need in our fight
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.50,0:25:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is a burning determination to do whatever it takes to fulfill our destiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.38,0:25:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing any of that \Namong you, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.82,0:25:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just yelling at us again...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.63,0:25:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Same old story every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.33,0:25:58.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wish we could talk more calmly... \NThe atmosphere here is so hostile.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.87,0:26:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you people to get your priorities straight and decide
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.10,0:26:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're prepared to see it through to the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.50,0:26:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, we need your next manuscript soon. {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.01,0:26:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.85,0:26:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all slacking off!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.62,0:26:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got work to do, \Nwe've no time for crybabies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.70,0:26:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of whining is no excuse!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.11,0:26:22.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still can't get over \Ntheir pretense of heroism...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.28,0:26:26.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,But taking away their authority won't accomplish anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.41,0:26:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.84,0:26:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.47,0:26:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.08,0:26:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Try not to dwell on it for too long. \NCommon Path can't be achieved in a day. {no clue what he means: あまり遅くならないようにな広宣流布は長丁場だ - don't do it too late, kousen rufu is a long stretch; long haul; marathon; time-consuming work}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.58,0:26:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The shallow, thoughtless \Nand reckless gung-ho bravery
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.67,0:26:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,won't amount to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.02,0:26:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.40,0:27:03.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Shinichi looked worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.69,0:27:07.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,He must be having a hard time \Nadapting to that atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.19,0:27:11.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Many serious young people \Nprobably feel the same way about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.25,0:27:13.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,But it's those young people \Nwho are our strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.75,0:27:16.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, even if we suddenly change our modus operandi...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.54,0:27:24.08,Sign,,0,0,0,,Several days later
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.64,0:27:29.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.77,0:27:34.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,We have to make something good \Nfor the kids to enjoy...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.37,0:27:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.70,0:27:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A pleasure to see you \Nbeing so energetic, Shin-Chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.61,0:27:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm assigning the work \Nfor the next issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.32,0:27:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.37,0:27:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! That's what I'm here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.18,0:28:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.49,0:28:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.33,0:28:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to discuss something.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.10,0:28:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get seated first.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.81,0:28:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.94,0:28:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to speak frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.30,0:28:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I just can't bring myself to get along with Soka Gakkai's executives...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.90,0:28:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or even the Society itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.82,0:28:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You're at odds with Soka Gakkai?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.56,0:28:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid that might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.05,0:28:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.58,0:28:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how about this, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.58,0:28:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like it, why don't you try to make it a Soka Gakkai that you can like?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.77,0:28:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.07,0:28:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A true revolutionary would fight earnestly \Nto build an ideal Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.02,0:28:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need armchair intellectuals, who only criticize in their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.09,0:28:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,without taking action!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.07,0:29:05.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,Somehow, sensei knew exactly what I was feeling at that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.10,0:29:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.08,0:29:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes an organization enjoyable \Nis the variety of people in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.29,0:29:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, there will be some who make you think you'll never be able to work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.86,0:29:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the people like them \Nwho allow us to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.04,0:29:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,An organization made up entirely of similar people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.87,0:29:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will go to rack and ruin in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.72,0:29:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The history knows \Ncountless examples of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.31,0:29:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.67,0:29:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.42,0:29:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn't understand anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.72,0:29:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All of our comrades have come together in this Latter Day of the Law,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.04,0:29:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,each with their own role to play \Nin the fate of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.73,0:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we proceed to let those people's talents unfold fully?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.31,0:30:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, how can we make Soka Gakkai a strong and respectable organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.97,0:30:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Deciding that is your role. {kimitachi but idk who else he refers to}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.47,0:30:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.45,0:30:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.00,0:30:16.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Aobaso, an apartment in Omori where Shinichi Yamamoto moved to {山本伸一が移り住んだ大森のアパート「青葉荘」}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.16,0:30:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei gave me a scolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.95,0:30:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my own fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.84,0:30:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I must reflect on my actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.13,0:30:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to believe in him
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.81,0:30:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep working hard, \Nno matter for how long.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.59,0:30:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I must always reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.69,0:30:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on my own wrongdoings
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.56,0:30:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a revolutionized person. {unsure, maybe "someone who can start a revolution"}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.39,0:30:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.87,0:30:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't have anyone else to look at,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.97,0:30:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,except your own pitiful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.60,0:30:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,, Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.84,0:31:06.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Young Yamamoto's life \Nshone like the morning sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.01,0:31:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to build an ideal Soka Gakkai \Nthat everyone can love and relate to."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.26,0:31:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"No matter what trials and tribulations I face, I'll do it!" - he vowed to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.00,0:31:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wouldn't be long before Toda Josei and Yamamoto Shinichi were faced
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.20,0:31:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with a mountain of tribulation by far exceeding anything they could have ever imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.89,0:31:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The drama between master and disciple emerges from the neverending daily struggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.51,0:31:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wouldn't be until after they've overcome all those struggles... {[that they reach nirvana or something]}
